        "description": "This project details the construction of a flame-throwing robot using Arduino and various electronic and mechanical components. The robot can be controlled via Bluetooth and is designed to be relatively inexpensive and easy to build, although caution is advised due to the use of fire.",
        "steps": [
            "Gather all the necessary electronic components, shop-bought items, bathroom supplies, and tools as listed in the components and tools section.",
            "Design the circuit using a breadboard, taking into account the current consumption of the servo motors to prevent Arduino reboots. The servo triggers the deodorant and rotates the ultrasonic sensor, while a TIP31C (or TIP120) controls the electric arc of the lighter.",
            "Solder the circuit components onto the PCB, dividing it into two boards: one for the L293D motor driver and the other for the Arduino. Ensure all GND connections are wired together and that the correct voltages are supplied to each component.",
            "Construct the chassis by cutting and assembling steel sheets and brass pipes. Drill holes for mounting components like the deodorant, PCB, and trolley wheel. Attach the motors to the sheet using epoxy and rivet the trolley wheel.",
            "Build the flame conduit using the medicine box and brass pipe. Create a waterproof seal with epoxy. Attach the TIP120 board and gas lighter circuit, taking precautions against short circuits. Construct a metal structure for the servo to hold the deodorant. Create a non-return valve by filling the medicine box with water.",
            "Upload the provided Robot.ino code to the Arduino Nano using the Arduino IDE. Install the 'Arduino BT Joystick' app on an Android phone and connect to the robot via Bluetooth using the HC-06 device. The app provides controls for movement, lights, and the flame thrower."
